{"id": "test-02600", "text": "They have 104 points, 15 ahead of USA I's Jim Herberich and breakman Garrett Hines who managed only 10th place on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 34, "end": 39, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "USA I"}, {"start": 42, "end": 55, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jim Herberich"}, {"start": 69, "end": 82, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Garrett Hines"}]}
{"id": "test-02601", "text": "SKIING-CHINESE MAKE PROMISING FREESTYLE SKIING DEBUT.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 14, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "SKIING-CHINESE"}]}
{"id": "test-02602", "text": "TIGNES, France 1996-12-07", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "TIGNES"}, {"start": 8, "end": 14, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "France"}]}
{"id": "test-02603", "text": "China made a promising debut on the freestyle skiing world cup circuit in an aerials event in the French resort of Tignes on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "China"}, {"start": 98, "end": 104, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "French"}, {"start": 115, "end": 121, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Tignes"}]}
{"id": "test-02604", "text": "While the Chinese failed to gain a place in the men's final, they had two in the top 10 of the women's competition, Cuo Dan finishing a respectable seventh and Xu Nannan ninth.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 10, "end": 17, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Chinese"}, {"start": 116, "end": 123, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Cuo Dan"}, {"start": 160, "end": 169, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Xu Nannan"}]}
{"id": "test-02605", "text": "But overall, it was France and Canada who dominated the day.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 20, "end": 26, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "France"}, {"start": 31, "end": 37, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Canada"}]}
{"id": "test-02606", "text": "Alexis Blanc and Sebastien Foucras gave France a one-two finish in the first aerials competition of the season.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 12, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Alexis Blanc"}, {"start": 17, "end": 34, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Sebastien Foucras"}, {"start": 40, "end": 46, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "France"}]}
{"id": "test-02607", "text": "Blanc collected his seventh career World Cup win with a two jump combined score of 238.36 points, easily beating Foucras, the overall World Cup aerials champion, who was a distant second with 223.60.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Blanc"}, {"start": 35, "end": 44, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "World Cup"}, {"start": 113, "end": 120, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Foucras"}, {"start": 134, "end": 143, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "World Cup"}]}
{"id": "test-02608", "text": "Canada's Jeff Bean, who had never finished higher than ninth in a World Cup event, made his first trip to the podium taking third place with a mark of 209.96.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Canada"}, {"start": 9, "end": 18, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jeff Bean"}, {"start": 66, "end": 75, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "World Cup"}]}
{"id": "test-02609", "text": "Veronica Brenner of Canada, who picked up her first career victory at Tignes last year, made it two wins in a row at the French resort taking first in the women's competition with a score of 170.42.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 16, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Veronica Brenner"}, {"start": 20, "end": 26, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Canada"}, {"start": 70, "end": 76, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Tignes"}, {"start": 121, "end": 127, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "French"}]}
{"id": "test-02610", "text": "Swiss skiers occupied the other two places on the podium, Karin Kuster taking second with 160.55 narrowly ahead of Evelyne Leu with 160.36.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Swiss"}, {"start": 58, "end": 70, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Karin Kuster"}, {"start": 115, "end": 126, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Evelyne Leu"}]}
{"id": "test-02611", "text": "BOBSLEIGH-WORLD CUP TWO-MAN RESULTS.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 19, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "BOBSLEIGH-WORLD CUP"}]}
